    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-23T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-23T03:00:00-05:00" n="595"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/1289b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-23T04:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 23, 1943—4 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. For Faymonville from Stettinius. In view of termination of supply of aluminum
                    from the United Kingdom, the following indicates action taken on Soviet request
                    for additional aluminum from the United States:</p>
                <p>For the first quarter of 1943, the President has granted an additional 3,500 long
                    tons above Protocol commitments which will consist of 1,300 long tons of ingot
                    and 2,200 long tons of sheet. During the first quarter the United States will
                    thereby supply a total of 9,500 long tons. During the second quarter the United
                    States will supply about 5,500 long tons to complete Protocol commitments. The
                    President has made no decision on the Russian request for additional aluminum
                    above the Protocol commitment in the second quarter. You will be informed as
                    soon as decision has been reached.</p>
                <p>Repeated to London. [Stettinius.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
